{
  "text": "We next analyzed the spliced type B\u0408 (Fig. 1C ) and unspliced type A (Fig. 1D) per RNA variants individually. Irrespective of day length, at 18\u00b0C the majority of per mRNA transcripts were type B\u0408 ( Fig. 2) [CITATION_1] . The relative abundance of type B\u0408 to type A (type B\u0408/type A ratio) at 18\u00b0C ranged from \u03f32-to 4.5-fold higher at the different photoperiods analyzed (Fig. 2 to 6 ). In more than 10 independent experiments, we observed that in wild-type flies the proportion of type B\u0408 transcripts changed as a function of time in LD cycles (e.g., Fig. 2 to 6 ). At all photoperiods analyzed (i.e., 6:18LD, 9:15LD, and 12:12LD), daily trough and peak values in the ratio of type B\u0408 to type A were significantly different (P \u03fd 0.0001 by Student's t test; n \u03ed 4) (Fig. 2 and data not shown). The most consistent trends in dmpi8 splicing oscillation were that the proportion of the spliced type B\u0408 variant was overall lower during the day, and as photoperiod was shortened it accumulated earlier and reached higher peak values in the night (Fig. 2) . These results suggest that the daily mean splicing of dmpi8 is more efficient under short photoperiods, consistent with the earlier accumulation phase and higher levels of total per mRNA ( Fig. 1B and E) .",
